headlines.description: — Kelly Oubre Jr. hit a career-high nine of Charlotte's franchise-record 24 3-pointers and the Hornets routed the Pistons 140-111 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oubre, Hornets set franchise record for 3s, rout Pistons

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid scored 31 points, Tobias Harris added 22 and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Orlando Magic 116-106 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid, Harris lift 76ers by Magic for fifth straight win

headlines.description: — Kevin Porter Jr. hit a 3-pointer from the right wing with 0.4 seconds left to give the Houston Rockets a 114-111 victory over the Washington Wizards on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porter hits 3 with 0.4 left, Rockets beat Wizards 114-111

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Gregg Popovich became the first to coach 2,000 NBA games with the same team, and Dejounte Murray scored 22 points to lead the San Antonio Spurs past the Boston Celtics 99-97 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray, Spurs hold off Celtics 99-97 in Popovich's 2,000th

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving scored 22 points and sparked Brooklyn to a big rally in the second half of his season debut, Kevin Durant had 39 and the Nets beat the Indiana Pacers 129-121 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving helps Nets charge past Pacers in his season debut

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry knows he didn't exactly honor the legacy of the NBA's best 7-foot 3-point shooter on the night the Dallas Mavericks retired Dirk Nowitzki's number against the Golden State Warriors.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Mavs beat Curry, Warriors 99-82 on Nowitzki's night

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 33 points, OG Anunoby and Gary Trent Jr. had 22 apiece and the Toronto Raptors beat the short-handed Milwaukee Bucks 117-111 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam scores 33 points, Raptors beat short-handed Bucks

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 17 points and 16 rebounds, while D’Angelo Russell struggled on 3-of-12 shooting in their return to the lineup for the Minnesota Timberwolves in a 98-90 win against the Oklahoma City Thunder on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns, Russell return; Timberwolves beat Thunder 98-90

headlines.description: — Bojan Bogdanovic scored a season-high 36 points and the Utah Jazz stretched their road winning streak to 10 games by beating the Denver Nuggets 115-109 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Roadies: Bogdanovic scores 36, Jazz beat Nuggets 115-109

events.name: Miami Heat at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — With Jimmy Butler sidelined by injury and Kyle Lowry ejected in the first half, Max Strus' return came at an opportune time for the Miami Heat.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat overcome Butler's absence in 115-109 win over Portland

headlines.description: — Kevin Huerter scored five of his 25 points in the final 38 seconds and the short-handed Atlanta Hawks held off the Sacramento Kings 108-102 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Huerter's late charge lifts Hawks over Kings 108-102
